{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-388","title":"优胜劣汰","sectionId":"chapter-17","sectionTitle":"探索生命爱自然","pageStart":1901,"pageEnd":1905,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":14,"duplicateEntryCount":25,"pages":[{"number":1901,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"388 优胜劣汰"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"natural selection 自然选择，物竞天择","headword":"natural selection"}]},{"number":1902,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"biophysical environment 生物物理环境","headword":"biophysical environment"},{"type":"entry","text":"environmental degradation环境退化","headword":"environmental degradation"},{"type":"entry","text":"weed out 淘汰","headword":"weed out"},{"type":"entry","text":"die out 消失","headword":"die out"}]},{"number":1903,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"food chain 食物链","headword":"food chain"},{"type":"entry","text":"morphological resemblance 形态相似","headword":"morphological resemblance"},{"type":"entry","text":"evolution [ˌiːvəˈluːʃn]","headword":"evolution"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.进化"},{"type":"entry","text":"evolutionary change 进化变异","headword":"evolutionary change"}]},{"number":1904,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"self-evident [ˌself ˈevɪdənt]","headword":"self-evident"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.显而易见的，不言而喻的"},{"type":"entry","text":"directional selection 定向选择","headword":"directional selection"},{"type":"entry","text":"develop rapidly迅速地发展","headword":"develop rapidly"},{"type":"entry","text":"energy metabolism能量代谢","headword":"energy metabolism"},{"type":"entry","text":"metabolite [məˈtæbəlaɪt]","headword":"metabolite"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.代谢产物"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"}]},{"number":1905,"blocks":[{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 1"},{"type":"example","text":"A：Because of human's behaviour, the habitats of animals are"},{"type":"text","text":"destroyed. Some of them are endangered. （由于人类的行为，动物的栖"},{"type":"text","text":"息地受到破坏。有些已经濒临灭绝。）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：Yes, we should better protect the environment. （是的，我们应"},{"type":"text","text":"该更好地保护环境。）"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 2"},{"type":"example","text":"A：If the extinction of the snakes was inevitable, rats would wantonly"},{"type":"text","text":"breeding. Then what can we do? （如果蛇的灭绝不可避免，那么老鼠将"},{"type":"text","text":"大肆繁殖。到那时候我们该怎么办？）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：So each has its biological significance of the existence. They are in"},{"type":"text","text":"the natural law of survival. If a food chain breaks, then another will"},{"type":"text","text":"wantonly breed animals, and even lead to a threat to humanity. We should"},{"type":"text","text":"bear in mind the protection of animals. （因此每一种生物都有它存在的"},{"type":"text","text":"意义，它们都在遵循自然的法则生存。如果生物链的一头断了，那么"},{"type":"text","text":"另一种动物就会大肆繁殖，甚至威胁到人类。我们要牢记保护动"},{"type":"text","text":"物。）"}]}]}